The article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on December 5, 2016, titled "Steps for Increased Legal and Policy Transparency Concerning the United States Use of Military Force and Related National Security Operations." In the memorandum, President Obama emphasizes the importance of transparency and his commitment to making information available to the Congress and the public regarding the US use of military force and national security operations. The memorandum directs national security departments and agencies to prepare a formal report describing key legal and policy frameworks guiding these operations, with the intention of releasing the report to the public. It also outlines the process for keeping the report updated and arranging for its public release on an annual basis. The memorandum defines "national security departments and agencies" and "related national security operations" and authorizes the Secretary of State to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.